          "descriptionModule": {
            "briefSummary": "The purpose of this study is to see if it is safe and effective to give T-20 to HIV-positive adults. T-20 is an anti-HIV drug.",
            "detailedDescription": "Patients are randomly placed into 1 of 6 groups: 4 dose levels of T-20 are given by subcutaneous infusion and 2 by subcutaneous injection. The entire study lasts 7 weeks; including a 2-week screening period, followed by 28 days of treatment and 1 week of follow-up."
          },
